Rocket.Chat.companyInfo: Rocket.Chat is the world’s largest open-source communication platform, trusted by 12M+ users in 150 countries. Improve team productivity and own your data with a flexible and transparent hub that allows companies to centralize communication and customer support in a single place. Highly-secure chat, video, audio, and file sharing for enterprises.

Runops.companyInfo: Runops prevents developers from blocking on Devops tasks. The company does this by letting any engineer do Devops work under the supervision of the Devops team. You can think of them as code review for Devops tasks.

Sami.companyInfo: Sami is a health insurance company using digital tools to increase quality and decrease costs of health plans. It's based on care coordination with a personal doctor, telemedicine, analytics and change of incentives for providers to offer trust and efficiency to its members. It fundamentally changes the value chain when it's able to provide better and cheaper at the same time, covering also benefits such as gyms and mental health.

Sanar.companyInfo: Sanar is a fast-growing Brazilian edtech company that provides high-quality affordable tools for healthcare professionals and students to improve their careers. The content developed by the company helps train nurses, nutritionists, psychologists, pharmacists, dentists, veterinarians, physiotherapists and physicians in over 4,000 cities across Brazil. Sanar's mission is to become the education hub for the healthcare professional throughout their life.

Vitalk.companyInfo: Vitalk is an AI-powered digital assistant for mental health that helps HR departments transform their company cultures to encourage mental wellness. Woba.companyInfo: Woba is targeting the multi-trillion dollar commercial real estate market that has been shifting to a flexible model (Office as a Service) with a unique three sided business model. Through an "office pass", the company allows users to book a workspace for as little as 30 minutes on very short notice with a pin code delivered to their smartphones.
